      "title": "Methods for generating high-resolution structural models from electron microscope tomography data",
      "abstract": "Summary More sophisticated model-generation methods are also available for EMT. One EMT software package, Reconstructed volumes generated by tilt-image elec- IMOD (Kremer et al., 1996), permits the creation of atron-microscope tomography offer the best spatial model contourat aparticular isodensitylevel ona series resolution currently available for studying cell struc- of virtual slices. General purpose commercial software tures in situ. Analysis is often accomplished by creat- applications such as Amira (ZIB, Indeed-Visual Con- ing surface models that delineate grayscale contrast cepts GmbH, Berlin, Germany) and AVS (Advanced Vi- boundaries.Here,weintroduceaspecializedandcon- sual Systems Inc., Waltham, MA) offer a plethora of venient sequence of segmentation operations for alternative segmentation, visualization, and analysis making such models that greatly improves their relia- methods. While these software packages each have bility and spatial resolution as compared to current their advantages and limitations, there remains a sub-"
